What is OOPS?

OOPS = Object-Oriented Programming System

It is based on 4 main concepts:

Encapsulation

Abstraction

Inheritance

Polymorphism

Abstraction means hiding implementation details and showing only important features.
When you use an ATM machine:

You insert card

Enter PIN

Select Withdraw

Get cash

üëâ You don‚Äôt know:

How bank server validates PIN

How balance is checked

How machine counts notes

How transaction is logged

You only see important features (Withdraw, Deposit, Check Balance).
The implementation is hidden.
